FBIS4-41264 "drsov121_f_94010" FBIS-SOV-94-121 Daily Report 23 Jun 1994 National Affairs Meshkov Appoints Representatives to Russia Meshkov Appoints Representatives to Russia LD2306100594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 23 Jun 94 LD2306100594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] Today, Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov issued edicts on appointing the republic's plenipotentiary representatives to Moscow and Russia and on opening Crimea's permanent mission in Krasnodar Kray. According to ITAR-TASS information, Meshkov also signed an edict on setting up a space information agency in Crimea. The leadership of the republic's parliament has adopted a decision on setting up a supreme economic council attached to the presidium of the Supreme Soviet.
